cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is related to computer vision (CV) as it deals with image understanding and object detection. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it generates descriptions of images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, specifically neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The attention mechanism used in the model is a popular technique in NLP, which makes cs.CL a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of LSTM units in the RNN suggests that cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) could also be a relevant sub-category.
